<td style="width:55%" VALIGN="TOP">
<div class="pageBody">
<p>The Collaborative Computational Project for electron cryo-microscopy (CCP-EM) supports users and developers in biological EM. The three principal aims are:
<ul>
<li>Build a UK community for computational aspects of cryo-EM. Provide a focus for the cryo-EM community to interact with
<a href="http://www.ccp4.ac.uk">CCP4</a>/<a href="http://www.ccpbiosim.ac.uk">CCPBioSim</a>/<a href="http://www.ccpn.ac.uk">CCPN</a>, and the broader international community.
<li>Support the users of software for cryo-EM through dissemination of information on available software, and directed training.
<li>Support for software developers including porting, testing, and distribution of software.
</ul>
The creation of CCP-EM is supported through a 3-year Partnership Grant from the MRC and continued support is provided through a new 5-year Partnership Grant from the MRC.
</p>

<p>There is a <font color="red">mailing list</font> for CCP-EM (supported by JISCMail). The home page for
the list is at
<a href="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk/CCPEM">https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk/CCPEM</a>. To subscribe to the list, click on "Subscribe or Unsubscribe" on this page. Once you have an account, you can manage your list preference from this page. You can also search the CCP-EM archive from here.
Note that the list is
<a href="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk/policyandsecurity/#7">PUBLIC</a>, meaning that the
archives can be accessed by anyone, and are indexed by search engines. For more details,
see the JISCmail <a href="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk/policyandsecurity/index.html">
Service Policies page</a>.</p>

<p><img src="images/Twitter_logo_blue.png" width=30>Follow us on Twitter
<a href="https://twitter.com/ccp_em">@ccp_em</a>.</p>

<p>Email us at <a href="mailto:ccpem@stfc.ac.uk">ccpem@stfc.ac.uk</a>.</p>

